{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.15.1515;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\b\f0\fs20 You can respond to the user moving from node to node. This is done by using the Record Prefix and Record Suffix events.\par
\par
Record Prefix is executed just before the user interacts with a record. For a Tree Control, this means that it will be executed just before the cursor lands on a node.\par
\par
Record Suffix is executed just as the user leaves a record. For a Tree Control, this means it will be executed just as the cursor leaves a node. \par
\par
However, Record Suffix is, by default, only executed if the record has been changed. For this example, Force Record Suffix has been set to Yes, so a message is given when the cursor leaves a node.\par
}
